# Performance Rules — obm_gen_with_ai

> Variables: See `_project_config.mdc`. Key values: `{{CONSUMER_BASE}}`, `{{SELECTOR_BASE}}`, `{{PROGRESS_LOAD}}`, `{{ON_START_HOOK}}`, `{{INIT_EVENT_LISTENER}}`, `{{PROVIDER_BASE}}`.

## Goals

- **Rebuild as little as possible** — only widgets that need the data rebuild.
- **No heavy work in `build()`** — no JSON parsing, no Dio calls.
- **Use `const` wherever possible** — compiler skips unchanged subtrees.

## Rebuild Optimization

| Scenario                             | Approach                                         |
|-------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Watch provider state                 | `{{CONSUMER_BASE}}<S,P>` (auto-switches on `currentState`) |
| Watch a specific field              | `context.select<T, R>((p) => p.field)`          |
| Inside callback / event handler     | `context.read<T>()` — NEVER `.watch()`           |
| Stateless widget with no state      | Use `const` constructor                          |

```dart
// BAD — watches entire provider → rebuilds on every notify
final p = context.watch<XxxProvider>();
return Text(p.items.length.toString());

// GOOD — watches only length field → rebuilds only when length changes
final count = context.select<XxxProvider, int>((p) => p.items.length);
return Text(count.toString());
```

## Widget Structure

1. **`build()` must be clean** — only `return Widget(...)`. Extract logic to `_buildXxx()` methods or separate widget classes.
2. **Separate Screen entry from Body widget:**
   - `XxxScreen extends {{SCREEN_BASE_CLASS}}` — declares generic types only.
   - `_XxxScreenState extends {{SCREEN_STATE_BASE}}<T,S,P>` — overrides `buildBody()`.
   - `BodyXxxWidget` (StatelessWidget) — real UI, watches state via `{{CONSUMER_BASE}}` / `context.select`.
3. **Max ~4 nesting levels** before extracting a widget.
4. **Initial data fetch** — put in `{{ON_START_HOOK}}` override so it runs from the provider constructor:

```dart
class XxxProvider extends {{PROVIDER_BASE}}<XxxService> {
  @override
  void {{ON_START_HOOK}}() {
    super.onStart();
    fetchItems();
  }
}
```

## Dispose

```dart
@override
void dispose() {
  _controller.dispose();
  _focusNode.dispose();
  _scrollController.dispose();
  // refreshController.dispose();  ← if using pull-to-refresh
  super.dispose();
}
```

`{{SCREEN_STATE_BASE}}.dispose()` already cancels the `Connectivity` subscription — only dispose controllers/streams you created.

## Async Safety

```dart
Future<void> _onSubmit() async {
  await context.read<XxxProvider>().submit();
  if (!mounted) return;
  context.read<XxxProvider>().showToast(
    {{I18N_CLASS}}.done,
    type: {{TOAST_TYPE_ENUM}}.success,
  );
}
```

## Image & List

| Rule                                                       | Reason                                    |
|------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| Local SVG → `{{SVG_HELPER}}(name, width:, height:)`       | Centralized SvgPicture wrapper            |
| Long list → `ListView.builder` / `.separated`             | Lazy item construction                    |
| Pull-to-refresh + load-more → `BaseLoadMorePage.generateList()` | `SmartRefresher` + `RefreshController` |
| Avoid `setState` inside `build`                            | Triggers infinite rebuild                 |
| `ListView` with `itemExtent` when items share the same height | Skips measure pass → smoother scroll  |

## Rebuild Boundaries

```dart
// GOOD — narrow rebuild scope per widget
class HeaderWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return {{SELECTOR_BASE}}<XxxProvider>(
      selector: (_, p) => p.title,
      contextParrent: context,
      onRepository: (ctx, repo) =>
          Text((repo as XxxProvider).title),
    );
  }
}

class ListWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return {{CONSUMER_BASE}}<XxxService, XxxProvider>(
      onRepositorySuccess: (repo) =>
          _ListContent(items: (repo as XxxProvider).items),
    );
  }
}
```

## DO / DON'T

| DO                                                    | DON'T                                               |
|-------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| `{{CONSUMER_BASE}}` auto-switches on `currentState`    | Plain `Consumer<P>` — requires manual state checks   |
| `context.read` in callbacks                            | `context.watch` in callbacks                       |
| `const` on stateless widget constructors              | Calling `X()` without `const`                     |
| `provider.{{ON_START_HOOK}}()` for initial data fetch  | Calling API inside `initState` directly             |
| Check `mounted` after `await`                          | `setState` / `Navigator.pop` after `await`          |
| `ListView.builder` for long lists                      | Unbounded `ListView` with thousands of items        |
| `{{SVG_HELPER}}()` for local SVG                      | `SvgPicture.asset(...)` called directly            |
| `provider.{{M_SHOW_PROGRESS}}()` for blocking operations | `{{PROGRESS_LOAD}}.showProgress(context)` from widget |

## Review Checklist

- [ ] Uses `{{CONSUMER_BASE}}` or `context.select` (not plain `Consumer`).
- [ ] Callbacks use `context.read`.
- [ ] `buildBody()` is under ~80 lines with no heavy logic.
- [ ] All Controller/FocusNode/Stream subscriptions are disposed.
- [ ] `mounted` checked after every `await` in StatefulWidget.
- [ ] Long lists use `.builder` / `.separated`.
- [ ] SVG assets loaded via `{{SVG_HELPER}}()`.
